responseCode.name: OK
responseCode.detail: Standard response for successful HTTP requests. The actual response will depend on the request method used. In a GET request, the response will contain an entity corresponding to the requested resource. In a POST request the response will contain an entity describing or containing the result of the action.

headers.name: accept-ranges
headers.description: Content-Types that are acceptable

headers.name: access-control-allow-headers
headers.description: Used in response to a preflight request to indicate which HTTP headers can be used when making the actual request.

headers.name: access-control-allow-origin
headers.description: Specifies a URI that may access the resource. For requests without credentials, the server may specify '*' as a wildcard, thereby allowing any origin to access the resource.

headers.name: access-control-expose-headers
headers.description: Lets a server whitelist headers that browsers are allowed to access.

headers.name: access-control-request-method
headers.description: Used when issuing a preflight request to let the server know what HTTP method will be used when the actual request is made.

headers.name: age
headers.description: The age the object has been in a proxy cache in seconds

headers.name: cache-control
headers.description: Tells all caching mechanisms from server to client whether they may cache this object. It is measured in seconds

headers.name: content-length
headers.description: The length of the response body in octets (8-bit bytes)

headers.name: content-type
headers.description: The mime type of this content

headers.name: date
headers.description: The date and time that the message was sent

headers.name: link
headers.description: Used to express a typed relationship with another resource, where the relation type is defined by RFC 5988

headers.name: server
headers.description: A name for the server

headers.name: status
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: strict-transport-security
headers.description: A HSTS Policy informing the HTTP client how long to cache the HTTPS only policy and whether this applies to subdomains.

headers.name: vary
headers.description: Tells downstream proxies how to match future request headers to decide whether the cached response can be used rather than requesting a fresh one from the origin server.

headers.name: via
headers.description: Informs the client of proxies through which the response was sent.

headers.name: x-cache
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-cache-hits
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-per-page
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-ratelimit-limit
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-ratelimit-remaining
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-request-id
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-runtime
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-served-by
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-timer
headers.description: Custom header

headers.name: x-total
headers.description: Custom header
